  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mary Brady reports on the activities of Henry C. Wright and Frederick Douglass. She says of H. C. Wright that &quot;we have greatly enjoyed his fireside society.&quot; She tells about his various meetings, including one attended by 700 or 800 children. Mary Brady says about Frederick Douglass: &quot;I feel almost afraid to trust myself to speak of this dear friend so highly do I estimate his moral &amp; intellectual character.&quot; She praises his speeches. H.C. Wright and Frederick Douglass left Leeds for New Castle to spend a few hours with Elizabeth Pease at Darlington.</subfield>
